Package: rblp
Type: Package
Title: BLP Demand Estimation for Differentiated Products
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Hyoungchul", "Kim", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "hchulkim@virginia.edu"),
    person("Jeff", "Gortmaker", role = "aut",
           comment = "Author of original pyblp Python package"),
    person("Chris", "Conlon", role = "aut",
           comment = "Co-author of pyblp methodology")
    )
Description: Estimate, simulate, and analyze demand for differentiated
    products using BLP-type random coefficients logit models (Berry,
    Levinsohn, and Pakes, 1995). Features include random coefficient
    mixed logit, nested logit, micro moments, demand and supply-side
    estimation via GMM, merger simulation, and counterfactual analysis.
    Translated from the 'pyblp' Python package by Conlon and Gortmaker
    (2020) <doi:10.1287/mksc.2023.1440>.
